Fire razed four dormitories at Ainabkoi Secondary School on Friday night, destroying property belonging to more than 200 students. Most students were in class for night preps. Eldoret East OCPD Robert Omanga on Saturday said the students who were in the dormitories were rescued and no one was injured. The cause of the fire is yet to be established. Students and neighbours at the tried in vain to put out the fire using water with firefighters arriving at the scene an hour after the incident. Teachers estimate property worth Sh2 milion was destroyed. Click here for the latest political news